HEADWORD: Subdominant
<hw>Sub*dom"i*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>The fourth tone above, or fifth below, the tonic; -- so called as
being under the dominant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subduable</ent>⟦br⟧
